      "info": {
        "contact": {
          "url": "https://opentdb.com"
        },
        "description": "The Open Trivia Database provides a completely free JSON API for use in programming projects. Use of this API does not require a API Key, just generate the URL below use it in your own application to retrieve trivia questions.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Open Trivia Database API Server",
            "url": "https://opentdb.com"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Trivia API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Fetch free, user-contributed multiple-choice and true/false trivia questions from the Open Trivia Database",
        "homepage": "https://opentdb.com",
        "docs_url": "https://opentdb.com/api_config.php",
        "license_short": "Questions are licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0).",
        "license_md": "- Trivia content is published by Pixeltail Games LLC under [CC BY-SA 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/).\n- You must credit the Open Trivia Database when redistributing questions.\n- Derivative works (e.g. modified question sets) must be shared under the same licence.\n- The API itself requires no key, but the licence terms apply to the question data you retrieve.",
        "about_md": "The [Open Trivia Database](https://opentdb.com) is a free, community-curated collection of over 5,000 verified trivia questions maintained by Pixeltail Games LLC. The JSON API at `https://opentdb.com` lets applications pull random questions for quizzes, games, and learning tools without an API key.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- Random questions via `GET /api.php` with parameters for `amount` (max 50 per call), `category`, `difficulty` (easy / medium / hard), and `type` (`multiple` or `boolean`).\n- A category lookup endpoint that returns the full list of available category IDs (General Knowledge, Science, Geography, History, Sports, Film, Music, Video Games, Anime, Mythology, and more).\n- Per-category and global question-count helpers.\n- Optional session tokens that remember which questions you have already received so the same question is not returned twice; tokens expire after 6 hours of inactivity and can be reset.\n- Selectable response encodings: default HTML entities, legacy URL encoding, RFC 3986, or Base64.\n\nOperational notes: no authentication is required, CORS is enabled, and the service enforces a 5-second cooldown per IP (response code 5 indicates rate limiting). Other documented response codes include 0 (success), 1 (no results), 2 (invalid parameter), 3 (token not found), and 4 (token exhausted).",
        "entity_desc": {
          "api": "Core question-retrieval and helper endpoints, including `GET /api.php` for random questions and the global question-count helper.",
          "api_category": "Category metadata: `GET /api_category.php` returns the list of available categories and their IDs, and `GET /api_count.php` returns the question count for a given category."
        },
        "auth": false
      },
